sql:
SELECT run_id, fitness
FROM optimization_runs
WHERE algorithm_type = 0;

external_knowledge:
- 'journey' metaphorically refers to the optimization runs;
- 'algorithmic guides' refers to the algorithms used in the optimization processes;
- 'secrets' corresponds to the descriptions of the algorithms, detailing their nature and purpose;
- 'expeditions' metaphorically represent the detailed descriptions of the algorithms, highlighting their use cases and functionalities.

sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) AS num_runs
FROM run_logs
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT algorithm_type, AVG(fitness) AS average_fitness
FROM optimization_runs
GROUP BY algorithm_type;

SELECT run_id, fitness, fevals, use_fast_mimic
     FROM optimization_runs
     WHERE time > (SELECT AVG(time) FROM optimization_runs);

external_knowledge:
- "significant optimization tasks" refers to problem types labeled as 'optimization';
- "large enough group" indicates a population size greater than 20;
- "high level of effectiveness" is defined by a fitness score above 50;
- "average performance metrics" involve calculating the average fitness and average execution time.
